Ecuador Beats Peru 2-1 at America Cup Soccer 
Ecuador kept their hopes of advancing to the quarter-finals alive when
they outplayed Peru 2-1 in a Group B match of the America Cup soccer
tournament in Rivera, Uruguay on Thursday.
Ecuador scored the two goals in the second half after Energio Diaz and
Jose Mora netted one goal each in the 62nd minute and 77th minute of
the match.
Ecuador's Maximo Tenorio scored an own-goal six minutes from the final
whistle to make the match score becoming 2-1.
After three matches in the Group B, Ecuador ranked third with one win
and two defeats, collecting 3 points.
The top two teams in each of the three first round groups qualify for
the quarter-finals. The two third-placed teams with the best records
also qualify.
